records.addlTxt: Original Transcript (23 pages) commencing 07/02/15 SENTENCING HEARING received and filed.
Request for payment of $17 witness fees for witness Jose V. processed and forwarded to the Treasurer's Office on check request x26212011 in court 1x on 8/18/15.

Attorney Richard L. Voss in court, defendant Demetrius Martel Camble not in court, in custody.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk  Parties have stipulated to restitution of $500.00 to Jose V. joint and several.  Amounts to be paid as previously ordered from 25% of the defendant's prison accounts.  Any unpaid amounts to convert to a civil judgment.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 5 YEARS with 75 days credit CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 3 YEARS.

Court finds defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration program and the WI Substance Abuse program.  

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- Absolute sobriety from drugs and alcohol.
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation department.
- No possession/consumption/selling/distribution of illegal drugs/alcohol.
- Random urine screens.
- Obtain/maintain fulltime employment/education/vocation.
- No contact with the victim named in the complaint or their residence.
- No contact with the co-actor
- Provide a DNA sample.
- Follow all rules of supervision and follow through with any other treatment deemed necessary by the department.

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
Restitution to be determined at a later date; 
All court costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA); 
All applicable fees of supervision.
-  No cash bail on deposit.
-  Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision. DOC shall collect those sums.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm. 
Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.
Court advised defendant that he may not vote until his civil rights have been restored.

Defendant Demetrius Martel Camble in court with attorney Richard L. Voss.  Defendant Demetrius Martel Camble in custody.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.

  Restitution hearing scheduled for August 18, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
